Hi Android team. I'm an American living in Japan using a Samsung GalaxyS5 running Android 6 in Japanese. I noticed today while using my phone that if you type in the word 外国人 (gaikokujin, foreigner), autocomplete offers an emoticon of a person with a big nose as a suggestion for input. This is similar to typing in ハッピー ("happy") and getting an option for a smiley face, except you know, racism. The same racist emoticon pops up if you type in 外人, which literally means outsider and is a racial epithet directed towards minorities. 

This is a preset feature, so I was wondering if you could help me understand where this racist smutt is coming from, and who to contact about it. (Pics or it didn't happen, so please see attached screencap.) Certainly the Android development team isn't espousing this sort of racism, right?

The butterfly effect: Perfect story from Istanbul

Dear #Android developers, i have a short story to share.

Last three weeks I have spent in North Vietnam to hiking in the mountains. Way home to Prague, I had bought a ticket with a transfer in Istanbul on 30th October. On this day in some European countries there is a shift of time, but in Turkey this year abolished the shift, but my phone synchronized time as if a shift has occurred and thus I missed my flight to Prague. It meant staying another day in Istanbul, where (because of my stupidity and probably some kind of drug in the tea) I has become a victim of typical fraud Istanbul. This scam has cost me around 2,000 dollars. So that's funny how man could ends if fully trust on your smartphone:) "Let's Have a Drink" Scam in Istanbul & Turkey Single Male robbery in Istanbul: what it is & how to avoid it, by Tom Brosnahan
